# Group Event Clusters

Event Clusters is a machine learning model that learns patterns in unstructured
data to automatically recognize, categorize and identify information from a
wide range of risk-related incidents breaking worldwide. Event Clusters are clusters of related Events. Each Feature
may or may not have additional Articles in the Cluster, this can be determined from the `cluster_size` value. Each Feature
will have a `cluster_id` value associated with the result and the articled defined in the `id` property and `source_url`
value will be the latest article within the cluster. This means that over time the values in these fields may change
but the `cluster_id` field will remain constant as that defines what the cluster is. Clusters are recalculated constantly and stabalize
after about 48hrs. 

The following are some of our Event Categories, this list is dynamic and will change:
 - Health
 - Terrorism
 - Natural Disasters
 - Unrest
 - Conflict
 - Transportation
 - Crime
 - Travel Warnings
 - Coup
 - Elections
 - Transnational Organized Crime (toc)
 
Articles can match to multiple event categories, even if you filter out a specific event it might still be matched in an article where there was a 90% or higher 
confidence of 2 or more events. New Event Models are currently being trained so this list will change from time to time.

For more information about how Event Clusters are created and how they work please see additional Documentation here: https://seerist.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BGS/pages/1562804251/Event+Clusters

## Event Clusters by Category [/v2/clusters/{event_category}?end={end}&start={start}&pageSize={pageSize}&pageOffset={pageOffset}&aoiId={aoiId}&bounds={bounds}&search={search}&severityMin={severityMin}&severityMax={severityMax}]

+ Parameters
    + `event_category` : `travel,unrest,transportation,health,terrorism,conflict,disaster,crime` (string, required) - Comma Separated List of Event Categories, possible values are: travel,unrest,transportation,health,terrorism,conflict,disaster,crime (or any combination)
    + `start` : `2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z` (string, optional) - Start Date of the Events (default start is end minus 24hours)
    + `end` : `2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z` (string, optional) - End Date of the Events (default is NOW)
    + `pageSize` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to return per page
    + `pageOffset` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to offset the results by, can be used for retrieving the next set of results up to 10,000
    + `aoiId` : us (string, optional) - AOI Identifier to limit the results from, this can be a GeoHash value, 2 Letter Country Code or City Code
    + `bounds` : `21.72,-130.30,50.58,-63.53` (string, optional) - Geospatial Bounding Box to restrict the search to
    + `search`: `search query` (string, optional) - Query string for article searches, see full documentation on how search terms work: https://seerist.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BGS/pages/1562804244/Searching+Events
    + `severityMin`: 0 (integer, optional) - Minimum severity of the article (0 - 10)
    + `severityMax`: 10 (integer, optional) - Maximum severity of the article (0 - 10)

### Event Clusters [GET]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            x-api-key: xxxx

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Events Response) 
    
## Event Articles [/v2/clusters/{cluster_id}/articles?pageSize={pageSize}&includeRoot={includeRoot}]
+ Parameters
    + `cluster_id` : `be5937b2-3cf1-4744-903a-50983ca189e9` (string) - Cluster ID to retrieve the articles of
    + `pageSize`: `10` (number, optional) - Max results to return
    + `includeRoot`: false (boolean, optional) - Whether not to include the representative (or root) article of the cluster.  This is the article returned from `/v2/clusters` call.

### Event Articles [GET]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            x-api-key: xxxx

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (EventArticles Response) 
    
