# Group World of Data

World of Data is used to query against all our documents clustered or not. Currently the endpoint removes all but the first instance of a cluster on a per page basis

## World of Data [/v1/wod?topic={?topic}&start={?start}&end={?end}&sources={?sources}&pageSize={?pageSize}&pageOffset={?pageOffset}&aoiId={?aoiId}&bounds={?bounds}&search={?search}&sortDirection={?sortDirection}&clusterId={?clusterId}&severityMin={?severityMin}&severityMax={?severityMax}&hotspotsOnly={?hotspotsOnly}&sectors={?sectors}&assets={?assets}&attackTypes={?attackTypes}&perpetrators={?perpetrators}&maritimeSubcategories={?maritimeSubcategories}&maritimeVesselTypes={?maritimeVesselTypes}&riskCategories={?riskCategories}&includeFilterCounts={?includeFilterCounts}&timestampProperties={?timestampProperties}]

+ Parameters
    + aoiId : `us` (string, optional) - AOI Identifier to limit the results from, this can be a GeoHash value, 2 Letter Country Code or City Code
    + assets: `1,2` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for asset types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of asset types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/asset-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-asset-types/verified-security-asset-types) endpoint
    + attackTypes: `35,1` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for attack types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of attack types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/attack-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-attack-types/verified-security-attack-types) endpoint
    + bounds : `21.72,-130.30,50.58,-63.53` (string, optional) - Geospatial Bounding Box to restrict the search to. 
    + clusterId: `7276a5ad-8125-4a6e-85bb-d11c1643bed6` (string, optional) - A cluster's id used to restrict results to just documents in that cluster
    + `end` : `2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z` (string, optional) - End Date of the documents (default is NOW)
    + `hotspotsOnly`: true (boolean, optional) - Retrieve only results that are part of a hotspot
    + `includeFilterCounts`: true (boolean, optional) - When enabled filter counts are included in the metadata portion of the response. These counts reflect the number of documents that would match a particular filter if you were to enable it
    + `maritimeSubcategories`: "47,48" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for maritime subcategories. Applicable only to verified documents with source of maritime. A list of maritime subcategories is available via the [/v1/config/verified/maritime/subcategories](#reference/helper-functions/verified-maritime-subcategories/verified-maritime-subcategories) endpoint
    + `maritimeVesselTypes`: "1,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for maritime vessel types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of maritime. A list of maritime vessel types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/maritime/vessel-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-maritime-vessel-types/verified-maritime-vessel-types) endpoint
    + `pageOffset` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to offset the results by, can be used for retrieving the next set of results up to 10,000
    + `pageSize` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to return per page
    + `perpetrators`: "8,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for perpetrators. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of perpetrators is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/perpetrators](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-perpetrators/verified-security-perpetrators) endpoint
    + `riskCategories`: `086211a8-6c52-4277-ba7c-792d392bca12,0af9a5ad-7733-4f9f-b3ce-707e7221f096` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for risk categories. Only applicable to sources: analysis or riskRatingChanges. A list of risk categories is available via the [/v1/config/risk-categories](#reference/helper-functions/risk-categories/risk-categories) endpoint
    + `search`: `search query` (string, optional) - Query string for article searches, see full documentation on how search terms work: https://seerist.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BGS/pages/1562804244/Searching+Events
    + `sectors`: "1,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for sectors. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of sectors is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/sectors](#reference/helper-functions/verified-sectors/verified-security-sectors) endpoint
    + `severityMax`: 10 (integer, optional) - Maximum severity of the article (0 - 10)
    + `severityMin`: 0 (integer, optional) - Minimum severity of the article (0 - 10)
    + `sortDirection`: `asc` (string, optional) - Direction to sort results. Results are sorted by timestamp
    + `sources` : `news,political` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of Sources. Available sources: `news, twitter, telegram, instagram, facebook, reddit, youtube, weibo, vk, toutiao, political, maritime, riskRatingChanges, evacuations, elections, analysis`
    + `start` : `2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z` (string, optional) - Start Date of the documents (default start is end minus 24hours)
    + `topic` : `travel,unrest,transportation,health,terrorism,conflict,disaster,crime` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of Event Categories, possible values are available via the [v1/config/topics](#reference/helper-functions/topics/topics-config) endpoint where the apiName property is the name to request a topic by
    + `timestampProperties` : `@completed` (string, optional) - Allows filtering by the @completed field using start and end parameters

### World of Data [GET]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            x-api-key: xxxx

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (WoD Response) 
    

## World of Data: Saved Search [/v1/wod/savedsearch/{savedSearchId}/execute?topic={topic}&sources={sources}&start={start}?end={end}&pageSize={pageSize}&pageOffset={pageOffset}&aoiId={aoiId}&bounds={bounds}&search={search}&sortDirection={sortDirection}&clusterId={clusterId}&pois={pois}&poisDistUnits={poisDistUnits}&hotspotsOnly={hotspotsOnly}&sectors={sectors}&assets={assets}&attackTypes={attackTypes}&perpetrators={perpetrators}&maritimeSubcategories={maritimeSubcategories}&maritimeVesselTypes={maritimeVesselTypes}&riskCategories={riskCategories}&clusterRootOnly={clusterRootOnly}&emotions={emotions}&forMap{forMap}&places={places}&placesDistUnits={placesDistUnits}&polygon={polygon}&precision={precision}&severityMin={severityMin}&severityMax={severityMax}&sortField={sortField}&sourceMetadataCountryOfFocus={sourceMetadataCountryOfFocus}&sourceMetadataCountryOfOrigin={sourceMetadataCountryOfOrigin}&sourceMetadataFollowerCountBracket={sourceMetadataFollowerCountBracket}&sourceMetadataLanguage={sourceMetadataLanguage}&sourceMetadataMisinfoSusceptibility={sourceMetadataMisinfoSusceptibility}&sourceMetadataReliability={sourceMetadataReliability}&sourceMetadataSocialAuthenticity={sourceMetadataSocialAuthenticity}&sourceMetadataType={sourceMetadataType}&verifiedType={verifiedType}&eventType={eventType}&sentiments={sentiments}&since={since}]

Use a saved search to set the parameters used by World of Data. Parameters provided in the URI overwrite those of the saved search.

+ Parameters
    + `savedSearchId`: `be5937b2-3cf1-4744-903a-50983ca189e9` (string, required) - Saved search's ID
    + `aoiId` : `us` (string, optional) - AOI Identifier to limit the results from, this can be a GeoHash value, 2 Letter Country Code or City Code
    + `assets`: "1,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for asset types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of asset types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/asset-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-asset-types/verified-security-asset-types) endpoint
    + `attackTypes`: "35,1" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for attack types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of attack types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/attack-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-attack-types/verified-security-attack-types) endpoint
    + `bounds` : `21.72,-130.30,50.58,-63.53` (string, optional) - Geospatial Bounding Box to restrict the search to.
    + `clusterId`: `7276a5ad-8125-4a6e-85bb-d11c1643bed6` (string, optional) - A cluster's id used to restrict results to just documents in that cluster
    + `clusterRootOnly`: false (boolean, optional) - Only find articles where cluster_root=true
    + `emotions` : `anger,disgust,fear,joy,sadness,surprise` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of Emotions.
    + `end` : `2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z` (string, optional) - End Date of the documents (default is NOW)
    + `eventType`: `all` (string, optional) - Verified Event Types. [all, detected, verified]
    + `forMap`: false (boolean, optional) - Results will include a Geohash aggregation.
    + `hotspotsOnly`: true (boolean, optional) - Retrieve only results that are part of a hotspot
    + `maritimeSubcategories`: "47,48" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for maritime subcategories. Applicable only to verified documents with source of maritime. A list of maritime subcategories is available via the [/v1/config/verified/maritime/subcategories](#reference/helper-functions/verified-maritime-subcategories/verified-maritime-subcategories) endpoint
    + `maritimeVesselTypes`: "1,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for maritime vessel types. Applicable only to verified documents with source of maritime. A list of maritime vessel types is available via the [/v1/config/verified/maritime/vessel-types](#reference/helper-functions/verified-maritime-vessel-types/verified-maritime-vessel-types) endpoint
    + `pageOffset` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to offset the results by, can be used for retrieving the next set of results up to 10,000
    + `pageSize` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of results to return per page
    + `perpetrators`: "8,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for perpetrators. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of perpetrators is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/perpetrators](#reference/helper-functions/verified-security-perpetrators/verified-security-perpetrators) endpoint
    + `places`: [[1, 2, 3]] (array(number), optional) - Array of arrays representing places to search around. [lon, lat, radius]
    + `placesDistUnits`: `mi` (string, optional) - Distance units for radius of a place. Defaults to miles. 'km' and 'mi' supported
    + `pois`: [[1, 2, 3]] (array(number), optional) - Array of arrays representing points of interest to search around. [lon, lat, radius]
    + `poisDistUnits`: `mi` (string, optional) - Distance units for radius of pois. Defaults to miles. 'km' and 'mi' supported
    + `polygon`: [[1, 2], [2, 3]] (array(number), optional) - Array of arrays representing coordinates of a polygon. [lon, lat]
    + `precision` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of the precision specific to request for the map.
    + `riskCategories`: `086211a8-6c52-4277-ba7c-792d392bca12,0af9a5ad-7733-4f9f-b3ce-707e7221f096` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for risk categories. Only applicable to sources: analysis or riskRatingChanges. A list of risk categories is available via the [/v1/config/risk-categories](#reference/helper-functions/risk-categories/risk-categories) endpoint
    + `search`: `search query` (string, optional) - Query string for article searches, see full documentation on how search terms work: https://seerist.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BGS/pages/1562804244/Searching+Events
    + `sectors`: "1,2" (string, optional) - Comma separated list of numeric identifiers for sectors. Applicable only to verified documents with source of political. A list of sectors is available via the [/v1/config/verified/security/sectors](#reference/helper-functions/verified-sectors/verified-security-sectors) endpoint
    + `sentiments` : `negative,neutral,positive` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of Sentiments.
    + `severityMin` : 0 (integer, optional) - Number of the minimal severity in results return
    + `severityMax` : 10 (integer, optional) - Number of the maximum severity in results return
    + `since` : `2025-02-11T20:00:00.000Z` (string, optional) - Returns events that were created or changed since this date and time
    + `sortDirection`: `asc` (string, optional) - Direction to sort results. Results are sorted by timestamp
    + `sortField`: `asc` (string, optional) - Database field name to sort results.
    + `sourceMetadataCountryOfFocus` : `AO,AD`  (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of 2 Letter Country Code.
    + `sourceMetadataCountryOfOrigin` : `AU,AT` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of 2 Letter Country Code.
    + `sourceMetadataFollowerCountBracket` : `high,medium,low`  (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of Source Metadata Follower Count
    + `sourceMetadataLanguage` : `bs,bn`  (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of 2 Letter Country Code
    + `sourceMetadataMisinfoSusceptibility` : `AF,issueSpecific`  (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of 2 Letter Country Code in addition to the optional value ["issueSpecific"]
    + `sourceMetadataReliability` : `high,medium` (string, optional) -  Comma Separated List of Source Metadata Reliability , possible values are available ["high", "medium", "low", "unrated"]
    + `sourceMetadataSocialAuthenticity` : `authentic,inauthentic` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List, possible values are available ["authentic", "inauthentic", "untagged"]
    + `sourceMetadataType` : `academic/think tank,activist/extremist` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of Source Metadata Types
    + `sources` : `news,political` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of Sources. Available sources: `news, twitter, telegram, instagram, facebook, reddit, youtube, weibo, vk, toutiao, political, maritime, riskRatingChanges, evacuations, elections, analysis`. Please note that Seerist Essentials users are restricted to just verified events (political, maritime, riskRatingChanges, evacuations, elections, analysis) and documents that pertain to hotspots
    + `start` : `2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z` (string, optional) - Start Date of the documents (default start is end minus 24hours)
    + `topic` : `travel,unrest,transportation,health,terrorism,conflict,disaster,crime` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of Event Categories, possible values are available via the [v1/config/topics](#reference/helper-functions/topics/topics-config) endpoint where the apiName property is the name to request a topic by
    + `verifiedType`: `political` (string, optional) - Comma Separated List of Verified Types ["security", "maritime"]


        
### World of Data: Execute Saved Search [GET]
