    + Attributes (WoD Response)

## World of Data: News and Social [/v1/wod/&sources={?sources}{?sourceMetadataType}{?sourceMetadataReliability}{?sourceMetadataMisinfoSusceptibility}{?sourceMetadataSocialAuthenticity}{?sourceMetadataFollowerCountBracket}{?sourceMetadataLanguage}{?sourceMetadataCountryOfOrigin}{?sourceMetadataCountryOfFocus}{?start}{?end}{?pageOffset}{?pageSize}{?sentiments}{?emotions}{?search}]

Get news and/or social media data by using attributes associated with the source of that data.

+ Parameters
    + sources (array[string], required)
        + Example: `news,twitter`
        + Values
            + `news`
            + `twitter`
            + `telegram`
            + `instagram`
            + `facebook`
            + `reddit`
            + `youtube`
            + `weibo`
            + `vk`
            + `toutiao`
        
    + sourceMetadataType (array[string], optional)
        + Example: `academic/think%20tank`
        + Values 
            + `academic/think%20tank`
            + `activist/extremist`
            + `forum`
            + `humanitarian`
            + `labor%20union`
            + `official/government`
            + `other`
            + `political`
            + `state-controlled%20media`
            + `journalistic`

    + sourceMetadataReliability (array[string], optional)
        Our assessment of source reliability
        + Example: `high,medium` 
        + Values
            + `high`
            + `medium`
            + `low`
            + `unrated`

    + sourceMetadataMisinfoSusceptibility  (array[string], optional)
        + Example: `issueSpecific,AF,AL`
        + Values
            + `issueSpecific`
            + `AF`
            + `AL`

    + sourceMetadataSocialAuthenticity (array[string], optional)
        + Example: `authentic,inauthentic,untagged`
        + Values
            + `authentic`
            + `inauthentic`
            + `untagged`

    + sourceMetadataFollowerCountBracket (array[string], optional) 
        + Example: `high,medium,low`
        + Values
            + `high`
            + `medium`
            + `low`
    
    + sourceMetadataLanguage (array[string], optional) 
        The language the source is written in. ISO-639 codes
        + Example: `sq,ar`
        + Values
            + `sq`
            + `ar`
            + `zh-CN`
            + `etc.`

    + sourceMetadataCountryOfOrigin (array[string], optional) 
        Where the source is usually authored. ISO-3166-2 code, uppercase
        + Example: `AF,DZ`
        + Values
            + `AF`
            + `DZ`
            + `etc.`

    + sourceMetadataCountryOfFocus (array[string], optional)
        Where the source typically focuses. ISO-3166-2 code, uppercase
        + Example: `AF,DZ`
        + Values
            + `AF`
            + `DZ`
            + `etc.`
                
    + start (string, optional)
        + Example: `2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z`
        
    + end (string, optional)
        + Example: `2024-11-12T00:00:00.000Z`
        
    + pageOffset(integer, optional)
      Number of results to offset the results by, can be used for retrieving the next set of results up to 10,000 Example: 10.
    
    + pageSize (integer, optional)
      The number of results per page. Example: 5
  
    + sentiments (string, optional)
      Comma separated list of Sentiments. Example: negative,neutral,positive
  
    + emotions (string, optional)
      Comma separated list of Emotions. Example: anger,disgust,fear,joy,sadness,surprise
    
    + search (string, optional)
        URL encoded lucene syntax string for article searches.
        + Example: `potato%20%7C%20chicken`


