# Data Structures


## HotSpotBounds Response (object)
+ `metadata` (MetadataHotSpotBoundsType) - MetadataObject
+ `type` : FeatureCollection (string) - Will be fixed String 'FeaureCollection'
+ `features` (array[FeatureCollectionHotSpotBoundsType])

## HotSpot GeoHash Response (object)
+ `metadata` (MetadataHotSpotGeoHashType) - MetadataObject
+ `type` : FeatureCollection (fixed) - Will be fixed String 'FeaureCollection'
+ `features` (array[FeatureCollectionHotSpotGeoHashType])

## Pulse Response Region (object)
+ `metadata` (MetadataPulseType) - MetadataObject
+ `type` : FeatureCollection (string) - Will be fixed String 'FeaureCollection'
+ `features` (array[FeatureCollectionPulseRegionType])

## Pulse Response Country (object)
+ `metadata` (MetadataPulseCountryType) - MetadataObject
+ `type` : FeatureCollection (fixed) - Will be fixed String 'FeaureCollection'
+ `features` (array[FeatureCollectionPulseCountryType])

## MetadataHotSpotBoundsType (object)
+ `status` : success (string) - This will indicate if the call was successful or a failure
+ `statusCode` : 200 (number) - HTTP Status code of the response
+ `count` : 10 (number) - Count of results in the Features array
+ `total` : 139 (number) - Total number of results produced by the query, all can be retrieved via paging
+ `startDate` : `2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z` (string) - Start Date of the HotSpot Scores
+ `endDate` : `2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z` (string) - End Date of the HotSpot Scores
+ `bounds` : `-90,-180,90,180` (string) - Bounds the HotSpot scores are within
+ `prev` : url (string) - A url to the previous set of results, null if no prior results exist
+ `next` : url (string) - A url to the next set of results, null if no next results exist

## HotSpotHistogramType (object)
+ `key_as_string` : `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` (string) - Date of the results
+ `activity` (array[ScoreValues]) - Activity Score values for the day
+ `pulse` (array[ScoreValues]) - Pulse Scores for the day

## MetadataHotSpotGeoHashType (object)
+ `status` : success (string) - This will indicate if the call was successful or a failure
+ `statusCode` : 200 (number) - HTTP Status code of the response
+ `count` : 10 (number) - Count of results in the Features array
+ `total` : 139 (number) - Total number of results produced by the query, all can be retrieved via paging
+ `startDate` : 2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z (string) - Start Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `endDate` : 2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z (string) - End Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `bounds` : `null` (string) - In a GeoHash query it will be null
+ `prev` : url (string) - A url to the previous set of results, null if no prior results exist
+ `next` : url (string) - A url to the next set of results, null if no next results exist
+ `geohash` : ttt (string) - GeoHash associated with the Individual Results
+ `histogram` (array[HotSpotHistogramType]) - On a multi-day query this will include the outputs for each day, useful in a graph

## MetadataPulseType (object)
+ `status` : success (string) - This will indicate if the call was successful or a failure
+ `statusCode` : 200 (number) - HTTP Status code of the response
+ `count` : 10 (number) - Count of results in the Features array
+ `total` : 139 (number) - Total number of results produced by the query, all can be retrieved via paging
+ `startDate` : 2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z (string) - Start Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `endDate` : 2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z (string) - End Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `bounds` : `-90,-180,90,180` (string) - Bounds input as part of the query string
+ `prev` : url (string) - A url to the previous set of results, null if no prior results exist
+ `next` : url (string) - A url to the next set of results, null if no next results exist
+ `stats` (StatsType)

## MetadataPulseGeoHashType (object)
+ `status` : success (string) - This will indicate if the call was successful or a failure
+ `statusCode` : 200 (number) - HTTP Status code of the response
+ `count` : 10 (number) - Count of results in the Features array
+ `total` : 139 (number) - Total number of results produced by the query, all can be retrieved via paging
+ `startDate` : 2019-01-22T00:00:00.000Z (string) - Start Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `endDate` : 2019-01-22T23:59:59.999Z (string) - End Date of the Pulse Scores
+ `bounds` : `-90,-180,90,180` (string) - Bounds input as part of the query string
+ `prev` : url (string) - A url to the previous set of results, null if no prior results exist
+ `next` : url (string) - A url to the next set of results, null if no next results exist
+ `geohash` : ttt (string) - The GeoHash the Results are related to
+ `histogram` : xxx (string) - Ignore this, it is legacy and will be removed in future deployments

## MetadataPulseCountryType (object)
