## StatsType (object)
Overall Stats for the response collection
### Properties
+ `total` : 123.456 (number) - total count in query
+ `max` : 5.2 (number) - max count in query
+ `avg` : 0.13 (number) - average count in query
+ `min` : `-12.13` (number) - min count in query

## FeatureCollectionHotSpotBoundsType (object)
+ `type` : Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (HotSpotBoundsType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## HotSpotBoundsType (object)
+ `geohash` : zu4 (string) - GeoHash Level 3 Grid the results belong in
+ `topics` (array[hotspotTopic]) - List of Topics that triggered this hotspot, the enum below is an example, there could be more or less than shown
+ `clusterIds` : guid (array[string]) - Array of clusterIds that triggered this hotspot, using the [World of Data](#reference/world-of-data) endpoint with the cluster id, i.e. v1/wod?clusterId={clusterId}, to retrieve source articles
+ `hotspotTypes` (array[hotspotType]) - Type of Hotspot (covid19 or top)
+ `location_metadata` (LocationMetadata)
+ `trigger_start`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Date/Time the hotspot was first created
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Start Time is when a hotspot crosses a day boundry. You can take startTime - age_in_hours and it will equal trigger_start. This is the field the start/end parameters use for the query filter.
+ `keywords` : police (array[string]) - List of keywords calculated for this hotspot
+ `age_in_hours` : 12 (number) - The age of this hotspot is Hours, HotSpots can persist indefinitely as long as the news cycle is still reporting on the events that initially triggered it.

## LocationMetadata (object)
+ `country` : `Republic of Belarus` (string, optional) - Full Name of the Country this Hotspot is in (optional)
+ `city` : `Minsk` (string, optional) - Full Name of the City this Hotspot is in (optional)
+ `countryCode` : `by` (string, optional) - ISO3166-2 Country Code (optional)
+ `state` : `Horad Minsk` (string, optional) - Full State Name this hotspot is in (optional)
+ `pop_country` : 327167434 (number, optional) - Population of the Country (optional)
+ `pop_city` : 42620 (number, optional) - Population of the City (optional)
+ `pop_state` : 1316216 (number, optional) - Population of the State (optional)

## FeatureCollectionHotSpotGeoHashType (object)
+ `type` : Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (HotSpotGeoHashType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## HotSpotGeoHashType (object)
+ `geohash` : zu4 (string) - GeoHash Level 3 Grid the results belong in
+ `hotspot`: netural - Value of the Hotspot: positive, netural, negative
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Date of the HotSpot value
+ `subscores` (string) - IGNORE
+ `activity` (ScoreValues)
+ `pulse` (ScoreValues)

## FeatureCollectionPulseType (object)
+ `type` : Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (PulsePropertiesType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## FeatureCollectionPulseRegionType (object)
+ `type`: Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (PulsePropertiesType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## FeatureCollectionPulseCountryType (object)
+ `type`: Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (PulsePropertiesCountryType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## FeatureCollectionPulseCountryCodeType (object)
+ `type`: Feature (fixed) - Will be 'Feature'
+ `properties` (PulsePropertiesCountryCodeType)
+ `geometry` (Geometry)

## PulsePropertiesCountryType (object)
+ `id`: af (string) - identifier for the location.  For Pulse Countries this is the ISO-3166-1 Alpha 2 Country Code
+ `country`: af (string) - ISO-3166-1 Alpha 2 Country Code associated with the results
+ `stability_score` (StabilityScoreCountryType)
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Date of the Pulse value
+ `subscores` (string) - IGNORE
+ `forecast` (array[ForecastType])
+ `color`: #feffd1 (string) - hexcode of the color used to represent the category of the score.  This color is based on the value in `stability_score.gauge`

## PulsePropertiesCountryCodeType (object)
+ `id`: af (string) - identifier for the location.  For Pulse Countries this is the ISO-3166-1 Alpha 2 Country Code
+ `country`: af (string) - ISO-3166-1 Alpha 2 Country Code associated with the results
+ `stability_score` (StabilityScoreCountryType)
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Date of the Pulse value
+ `subscores` (string) - IGNORE

## StabilityScoreCountryType
Scores (count and score) provide microtrends in an area and allow for detection of anomalies.
### Properties
+ `score`: 53.1 (number) - This is the locations current Pulse Score
