## PulsePropertiesType (object)
+ `id`: zu4 (string) - identifier for the location.  For Pulse Regions this is same as `geohash`
+ `geohash`: zu4 (string) - GeoHash Level 3 Grid the results belong in
+ `stability_score` (StabilityScoreType)
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-10T00:00:00.000Z` - Date of the Pulse value
+ `locations` (array[LocationsType])
+ `subscores` (string) - IGNORE
+ `forecast` (array[ForecastType])

## PulseDelta (object)
Changes in the score over different time periods
### Properties
+ `1`: `7.1` (number) - Difference between the current Pulse score and the previous day's score
+ `7`: `-26.2` (number) - Difference between the current Pulse score and the score from 7 days prior
+ `30`: `-20.3` (number) - Difference between the current Pulse score and teh score from 30 days prior

## PulseScoreGauge (enum)
+ `very_low`
+ `low`
+ `normal`
+ `high`
+ `very_high`

## ScoreValues
+ `count`: 3 - Cumulative score value. This is value takes into account not only information from startTime, but also information over time
+ `score`: 90.3 -  Percentile rank of stability_score.count vs the historical values over a period of time.

## StatsPtcType
+ `percentiles` (PercentilesType)
+ `min`: `-12.132` (number) - minumum value for a period of historic time for the startTime 0th percentile
+ `max`: 6.5 (number) - maximum value for a period of historic time for the startTime 100th percentile

## PercentilesType
Score/Count at the Percentile Rank's listed.
### Properties
+ `very_high`: `3.76` (number) - value at 90%
+ `high`: `-1.01` (number) - value at 25%
+ `low`: `-2.06` (number) - value at 10%
+ `very_low`: `-7.82` (number) - value at 2%

## PulseScoreAdjustments
(model v2 only) EventsAI security adjustments made from the baseline that gave use our final score (sum is baseline_delta value)
### Properties
+ `conflict`: `3.1` (number) - Conflict score adjustments from baseline
+ `crime`: `-6.1` (number) - Crime score adjustments from baseline
+ `terrorism`: `1.6` (number) - Terrorism score adjustments from baseline
+ `unrest`: `-5.6` (number) - Civil Unrest adjustments from baseline

## PulseEventCountsType
(model v2 only) Document counts and averages that drove the Pulse score adjustments
### Properties
+ `name` (PulseEventNames)
+ `actual`: `100` (number) - Actual count of event documents
+ `expected`: `50.2` (number) - Seasonal weighted average of document counts
+ `expected_upper`: `77.2` (number) - Upper bound of expected document count range
+ `expected_lower`: `20.4` (number) - Lower bound of expected document count range

## PulseEventNames (enum)
+ `all` - Counts and averages for documents
+ `conflict` - Counts and averages for Conflict events
+ `crime` - Counts and averages for Crime events
+ `terrorism` - Counts and averages for Terrorism events
+ `unrest` - Counts and averages for Civil Unrest events

## LocationsType
Locations Array will contain all the Country Names and Codes the Results falls within
### Properties
+ `country`: Russia (string) - Country Name
+ `code`: ru (string) - ISO-3166-1 Alpha 2 Country Code

## ForecastType (object)
This is an optional object that will only be returned if includeForecast=true in the Query params
### Properties
+ `startTime`: `2019-04-12T00:00:00.000Z` - Date the Forecast start on, usually Today+1day
+ `upper` (ForecastValueType)
+ `lower` (ForecastValueType)
+ `mean` (ForecastValueMeanType)

## ForecastValueType
Upper is 95th Percentile
Lower is 5th Percentile
### Properties
+ `count`: 0.38 (number) - Cumulative score value. This is value takes into account not only information from startTime, but also information over time
+ `score`: 50 (number) - Percentile rank of stability_score.count vs the historical values over a period of time.

## ForecastValueMeanType
+ `count`: 0.38 (number) - Cumulative score value. This is value takes into account not only information from startTime, but also information over time
+ `score`: 50 (number) - Percentile rank of stability_score.count vs the historical values over a period of time.
+ `probability`: 1 (number) - Confidence Value for the Forecast Mean 0-1


