## GeometryPoint (object)
A geometry is a GeoJSON object where the type member's value is one of the following strings: "Point", "MultiPoint", "LineString", "MultiLineString", "Polygon", "MultiPolygon", or "GeometryCollection".

<http://geojson.org/geojson-spec.html#geometry-objects>

### Properties
- type: `point` (string, fixed) - Type of geometry (Point).
- coordinates (Position) - Coordinates of point


## Geometry (object)
A geometry is a GeoJSON object where the type member's value is one of the following strings: "Point", "MultiPoint", "LineString", "MultiLineString", "Polygon", "MultiPolygon", or "GeometryCollection".

<http://geojson.org/geojson-spec.html#geometry-objects>

### Properties
- type: `Polygon` (string, fixed) - Type of the geometry (Polygon).
- coordinates (array[Polygon], required) - The structure for the elements in this array is determined by the type of geometry.

## Position (array, fixed)
- 0 (number)
- 0 (number)
- 0 (number, optional)
A single position.

### Items
- *0.0* (number, required) - northing / longitude
- *0.0* (number, required) - easting / latitude
- *0.0* (number, optional) - altitude)

## Line String (Geometry)

### Properties
- type: LineString (string, fixed)
- coordinates (array, required)
    - (Position, required)
    - (Position, required)
    - (Position, optional)

## LinearRing Coordinates (array)
A LinearRing is closed LineString with 4 or more positions. The first and last positions are equivalent (they represent equivalent points). Though a LinearRing is not explicitly represented as a GeoJSON geometry type, it is referred to in the Polygon geometry type definition.

### Items
- (Position, required)
- (Position, required)
- (Position, required)
- (Position, required)

## Polygon (object)
Coordinates of a Polygon are an array of LinearRing coordinate arrays. The first element in the array represents the exterior ring. Any subsequent elements represent interior rings (or holes).

### Properties
- type: Polygon (string, fixed)
- coordinates (array[LinearRing Coordinates], required) - an array of LinearRing coordinate arrays. For Polygons with multiple rings, the first must be the exterior ring and any others must be interior rings or holes.

